&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re looking for a &lt;strong&gt;Tech Lead &lt;/strong&gt;to own the technical direction, architecture, and engineering delivery of the Fraud subdomain within BVNK&#39;s FinCrime domain.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At BVNK, the Tech Lead is a technical guardian, hands-on in the codebase, accountable for the squad&#39;s technical health. You&#39;ll own the technical side (architecture, code quality, practices, risk). Your leverage comes from multiplying the team&#39;s capability building independent decision-making across the squad, not becoming the sole bottleneck.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The FinCrime domain protects the integrity of BVNK&#39;s platform, customers, and partners by preventing, detecting, and responding to financial crime risk across all products and geographies. It provides a consistent, policy-driven decision layer for risk across onboarding, transactions, and ongoing customer lifecycle events, screening providers, transaction monitoring, and fraud controls. Within this domain, the Fraud subdomain is responsible for building the detection, prevention, and response capabilities that protect BVNK from account takeovers, payment fraud, APP (Authorised Push Payment) fraud, card fraud, scams, and abuse across both fiat and crypto rails.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a greenfield technical leadership opportunity at a critical moment. BVNK is building a comprehensive, data-driven fraud detection and prevention framework that can scale with the company&#39;s rapid growth into new products and new markets..&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You&#39;ll define the technical architecture, lead the integration of Unit21 as BVNK&#39;s fraud engine, and build the engineering practices and standards that turn fraud prevention from a gap into a competitive advantage.&lt;/p&gt;
